Golly.

@Joshua 

The concept that there's any significance to certain words crossing or appearing close to each other is ridiculous, unless such proximity is somehow related to a theme.

I think, my friend, you're looking for something, much like Gertrude Stein's Oakland, that isn't there.

@MExpat 

I think vicious cycle and vicious circle are essentially the same idea, the former a recurrence in time, the latter a recurrence in space.

We all have our pet peeves, and most of them are irrational, or at least blown out of proportion.  I think yours is, as well.

